{
  "stem": "19210.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And many people were out because in the-- I was one of those that I couldn't stand these-- these waves, you know, and I was relieving myself with others when the-- a wave took a hold of one-- a young child, a young refugee, and swept him across.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And I jumped and I grabbed a hold of this guy and I-- I-- I-- you might say I saved him from the possibility of going overboard.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And his father then came to me and wanted to kiss my feet.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "It was so touching.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I didn't allow him that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But there were some scary moments, but we ended up ultimately arriving well in Palestine, in Eretz Israel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, a lot of-- of these children that left Portugal I believe was done through the influence-- other than the American Joint, the HIAS and the Jewish Community of Lisbon-- there was another group, the Youth Aliyah movement.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this group was-- they-- I don't know if you can call it the brainchild is the right world of an American lady, a Jewish lady, by the name of Henrietta Szold, S-Z-O-L-D.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was referred to as the mother of the Youth Aliyah movement.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And again, I was very privileged, very honorable, to meet with her personally at the Maon [INAUDIBLE] in Haifa.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maon is spelled M-A-O-N, Maon [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because I was already over the age of the groups that they like to keep in the Youth Aliyah movement.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So instead of going with them to the camp, I was sent to Kibbutz Beit Alpha and I stayed there for a little while before I left.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, absolutely.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, they didn't-- they didn't come to mean and influence me personally.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I wanted to go, my brothers wanted to go.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
